  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.58,
      "end": 5.48,
      "text": "This is a Libra Fox recording. All Libra Fox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.3,
      "end": 11.1,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit Libra Fox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.14,
      "end": 14.96,
      "text": "ESOP's fables. The Fox without detail.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 16.64,
      "end": 22.76,
      "text": "A fox once fell into a trap, and after a struggle managed to get free, but with the loss of his brush.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 23.64,
      "end": 28.2,
      "text": "He was then so much ashamed of his appearance that he thought life was not worth living",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 28.2,
      "end": 35.5,
      "text": "unless he could persuade the other foxes to part with their tails also, and thus devour attention from his own loss.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 36.24,
      "end": 41.0,
      "text": "So he called a meeting of all the foxes and advised them to cut off their tails.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 41.78,
      "end": 44.24,
      "text": "They're ugly things anyhow, he said.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 44.86,
      "end": 49.58,
      "text": "And besides, they're heavy, and it's tiresome to be always carrying them about with you.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 50.16,
      "end": 51.96,
      "text": "But one of the other foxes said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 51.96,
      "end": 58.04,
      "text": "my friend, if you hadn't lost your own tail, you wouldn't be so keen on getting us to cut off ours.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 59.32,
      "end": 61.86,
      "text": "End of The Fox without a tail.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
